theorem Topology.interior_diff_interior_eq_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (A \ interior A) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  apply Set.eq_empty_iff_forall_not_mem.2
  intro x hx
  rcases mem_interior.1 hx with ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hU_subset⟩
  -- From `U ⊆ A \ interior A` we deduce `U ⊆ A`.
  have hU_subset_A : U ⊆ A := fun y hy => (hU_subset hy).1
  -- Hence `x ∈ interior A`.
  have hx_intA : x ∈ interior A :=
    mem_interior.2 ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hU_subset_A⟩
  -- But `x ∉ interior A` since `x ∈ A \ interior A`.
  have hx_not_intA : x ∉ interior A := (hU_subset hxU).2
  exact (hx_not_intA hx_intA).elim

theorem Topology.interior_diff_self_interior_eq_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} : interior (A \ interior A) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hx
    rcases mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds.1 hx with ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hU_subset⟩
    -- `U` is an open set with `x ∈ U ⊆ A \ interior A`.
    have hU_subA : U ⊆ A := fun y hy => (hU_subset hy).1
    -- Any open set contained in `A` is contained in `interior A`.
    have hU_sub_intA : U ⊆ interior A := interior_maximal hU_subA hU_open
    have hx_intA : x ∈ interior A := hU_sub_intA hxU
    have hx_not_intA : x ∉ interior A := (hU_subset hxU).2
    exact (hx_not_intA hx_intA).elim
  · intro hx
    cases hx

theorem Topology.closure_diff_interior_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    closure (A \ interior A) ⊆ closure A := by
  -- The set difference `A \ interior A` is clearly contained in `A`.
  have hSub : (A \ interior A : Set X) ⊆ A := by
    intro x hx
    exact hx.1
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
  exact closure_mono hSub
